# F1 Fan Hub — Frontend

A simple frontend for F1 fans to track favourite drivers and teams, rate drivers, and view user reviews.

---

## Folder Structure
frontend/
│
├─ public/ # Public assets (images, icons, etc.)
├─ css/
│ ├─ dashboard.css
│ └─ login.css
├─ js/
│ ├─ login.js # Handles login form submission
│ ├─ dashboard.js # Handles dashboard interactions (ratings, favourites, reviews)
│ ├─ logout.js # Handles logout functionality
│ └─ nav.js # Navbar auth checks (can cause logout if misconfigured)
├─ index.html
├─ login.html
├─ dashboard.html
└─ README.md

---

## Quickstart

1. Clone the repo:
```bash

git clone <repo-url>
cd frontend

Start a local server (e.g., live-server or VS Code Live Server).

Make sure your backend is running at http://localhost:8787.

Open index.html in your browser.

##Features

User authentication (login, session cookies)

Dashboard:

Rate drivers (1–10 scale)

Mark favourite drivers and teams

##Known Issues

Dashboard sections may appear blank if not authenticated. Users are redirected to login.html.

Session persistence relies on cookies; if cookies are cleared, login is lost.

Navbar checks in nav.js can log users out unintentionally if misconfigured.

##Recommendations
Ensure you clear your cookie browser as this may affect the login process
To logout, click the f1 hub icon 
